  <description><![CDATA[<p>Ideally located just a five-minute walk from Piazza di Santa Maria Novella and the Basilica, Rivoli Boutique Hotel offers 50 years of excellent hospitality. This former 14th century Franciscan monastery is run by the warm and welcoming Caridi family. Their aim is to create a nostalgic Italian hotel which boasts original stone columns, coffered ceilings and spectacular arches and vaults that remain from its time as a monastery.</p>
<p>The enchanting and cosy atmosphere makes you feel instantly at home and the embellished and refined common areas such as the outdoor patio, with its blooming flowers and views of the surrounding colourful buildings, are perfect for kicking back with a book. Rooms here are spacious and sophisticated with relaxing hues of blue and gold and parquet flooring. After a long day of exploring the quaint, cobbled streets of this beautiful city, why not head back and take a dip in the amply sized whirlpool nestled in the small garden patio or book a table at the resident restaurant 'Benedicta' which boasts three Michelin forks and will tantalize your palette with some of the finest Mediterranean and Tuscan cuisine <a data-udi="umb://document/8b79e45930f145f6b156a9152415fa9b" href="/{localLink:umb://document/8b79e45930f145f6b156a9152415fa9b}" title="Florence">Florence</a> has to offer.</p>
<p>Transfer time: approx. 25 minutes by private car from Florence Airport or approx. 1 hour 10 mins by bus &amp; train or private car from Pisa Airport</p>]]></description>
